Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Backend Engineer position with Spotify. I bring over three years of professional experience in backend services, data infrastructure, and internal developer tooling, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect the technical depth and operational rigor this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected backend services for an analytics platform handling 1,000+ API endpoints, implementing contract testing and schema evolution patterns to ensure long-term maintainability across distributed systems — the same principles central to building and evolving Spotify's data analytics platform. To support teams building on this platform, I built internal developer tools and libraries (API-aware templates, SDK patterns, code-generation) that streamline data infrastructure API integration, accelerating developer onboarding and improving implementation correctness — directly mirroring the internal tooling and integration patterns this role will deliver. I also implemented a production-grade observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith for tracing, structured logs, and evaluation hooks, establishing SLOs and metrics-driven development practices that reduced latency by 60% and costs by 50%. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Java, Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis with data modeling for metadata schemas, handling file operations across Google Cloud Storage, S3, and MinIO — giving me direct experience with distributed datastores and backend service design. I also built internal developer tools including a support chatbot using LangChain and RAG with PostgreSQL vector store and analytical query patterns, reducing ticket resolution time by 20%, and contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using Spring Boot and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with service design, operational excellence, and SLO monitoring. Together, these roles have prepared me to build, operate, and evolve data analytics platforms and contribute meaningfully to Spotify's Data Infrastructure engineering organization.

